1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,019
China has achieved a remarkable milestone in artificial intelligence.

2
00:00:04,019 --> 00:00:13,397
Huawei's Ascend chip now controls 50 to 60 percent of China's domestic AI accelerator market, with projected revenues of $12 billion.

3
00:00:13,397 --> 00:00:20,542
At the same time, Tencent released Hi3, a massive 295 billion parameter model, completely for free.

4
00:00:20,542 --> 00:00:27,240
Let's explore how China is building a fully independent AI stack from silicon to software.

5
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:32,599
The chip war between Huawei and Nvidia is reaching a critical point.

6
00:00:32,599 --> 00:00:40,190
Huawei's Ascend 910C and upcoming 950 series are directly competing with Nvidia's offerings in the Chinese market.

7
00:00:40,190 --> 00:00:47,335
While Nvidia once dominated, Huawei has captured the majority share through aggressive development and government support.

8
00:00:47,335 --> 00:00:54,927
Chinese companies are increasingly choosing domestic chips over imported ones, driven by both policy and performance improvements.

9
00:00:54,927 --> 00:00:59,393
Beyond hardware, China is vertically integrating the entire AI stack.

10
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:09,217
Tencent's Hi3 model, with its mixture of experts architecture, demonstrates that Chinese AI models can compete with the best in the world.

11
00:01:09,217 --> 00:01:15,915
By making it free, Tencent is accelerating adoption and building an ecosystem around their technology.

12
00:01:15,915 --> 00:01:24,400
This combination of domestic chips running domestic models creates a self-sufficient AI infrastructure that doesn't depend on foreign technology.

13
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:28,419
China's chip and model dominance has significant geopolitical implications.

14
00:01:28,419 --> 00:01:37,350
With full control over both hardware and software, China can continue AI development regardless of export controls or trade restrictions.

15
00:01:37,350 --> 00:01:46,728
This independent AI stack positions China as a major force in the global AI landscape, reshaping the balance of technological power.
